The paper deals with image inpainting using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus is on high-resolution textures, which suggests that graphics (cs.GR) may also be a relevant sub-category. The use of CNNs for texture synthesis and optimization is also mentioned, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for patch-based image inpainting, which involves optimizing for texture statistics, indicating a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
